README.md

Analytics

   A curated list of amazingly awesome Erlang libraries, resources and
   shiny thing inspired by
   [https://github.com/h4cc/awesome-elixir]awesome-elixir.
     * Awesome Erlang
          + Package Management
          + Release Management
          + Configuration Management
          + Codebase Maintenance
          + Web Frameworks
          + Web Framework Components
          + HTTP
          + Testing
          + Logging
          + Monitoring
          + Deployment
          + Distributed Systems
          + Code Analysis
          + Build Tools
          + Geolocation
          + Debugging
          + Actors
          + Date and Time
          + ORM and Datamapping
          + Queue
          + Authentication
          + Text and Numbers
          + REST and API
          + Caching
          + Third Party APIs
          + Networking
          + Internet of Things
          + Algorithms and
            Datastructures
          + [file://localhost/Users/admin/Pros/sh/awesome/awe_raw/awesome-
            erlang#translations-and-internationalizations]Translations and
            Internationalizations
          + Miscellaneous
     * Resources
          + Websites
          + Books
          + Web Reading
          + Erlang Reading
          + Screencasts
     * Other Awesome Lists
     * Contributing

Package Management

   Libraries and tools for package and dependency management.
     * [https://hex.pm/]hex.pm - A package manager for the Erlang
       ecosystem.

Release Management

   Libraries and tools for release management.
     * [https://github.com/erlware/relx]relx - A release assembler for
       Erlang.

Configuration Management

   Libraries and tools related to configuration management.
     * [https://github.com/heroku/stillir]stillir - Cache environment
       variables as Erlang app variables.

Codebase Maintenance

   Libraries and tools to maintain a clean codebase.
     * [https://github.com/inaka/elvis]elvis - Erlang Style Reviewer.

Web Frameworks

   Web development frameworks.
     * [https://github.com/tsujigiri/axiom]Axiom - A micro-framework,
       inspired by Ruby's [https://github.com/sinatra/sinatra]Sinatra.
     * [https://github.com/ChicagoBoss/ChicagoBoss]ChicagoBoss - A server
       framework inspired by Rails and written in Erlang.
     * [https://github.com/ninenines/cowboy]cowboy - A simple HTTP server.
     * [https://github.com/kivra/giallo]Giallo - A small and flexible web
       framework on top of [https://github.com/ninenines/cowboy]Cowboy.
     * [https://github.com/mochi/mochiweb]MochiWeb - An Erlang library for
       building lightweight HTTP servers.
     * [https://github.com/synrc/n2o]N2O - WebSocket Application Server.
     * [https://github.com/nitrogen/nitrogen]Nitrogen - Framework to build
       web applications (including front-end) in pure Erlang.
     * [https://github.com/zotonic/zotonic]Zotonic - High speed, real-time
       web framework and content management system.

Web Framework Components

   Standalone component from web development frameworks.
     * [https://github.com/ChicagoBoss/cb_admin]cb_admin - An admin
       interface for Chicago Boss.
     * [https://github.com/dkuhlman/cb_websocket_controller]cb_websocket_c
       ontroller - A template for implementing a Websocket controller for
       ChicagoBoss.
     * [https://github.com/kivra/giallo_session]giallo_session - A session
       management library for the Giallo web framework.
     * [https://github.com/nitrogen/simple_bridge]simple_bridge - An
       abstraction layer providing a unified interface to popular Erlang
       web servers (Cowboy, Inets, Mochiweb, Webmachine, and Yaws).

HTTP

   Libraries for working with HTTP and scraping websites.
     * [https://github.com/ninenines/bullet]bullet - Simple, reliable,
       efficient streaming for Cowboy.
     * [https://github.com/ninenines/gun]gun - Erlang HTTP client with
       support for HTTP/1.1, SPDY and Websocket.
     * [https://github.com/benoitc/hackney]hackney - Simple HTTP client in
       Erlang.
     * [https://github.com/cmullaparthi/ibrowse]ibrowse - Erlang HTTP
       client.
     * [https://github.com/esl/lhttpc]lhttpc - A lightweight HTTP/1.1
       client implemented in Erlang.
     * [https://github.com/inaka/shotgun]shotgun - For the times you need
       more than just a gun.

Testing

   Libraries for testing codebases and generating test data.
     * [https://github.com/manopapad/proper]PropEr - A QuickCheck-inspired
       property-based testing tool for Erlang.
     * [https://github.com/esl/tracerl]tracerl - Dynamic tracing tests and
       utilities for Erlang/OTP

Logging

   Libraries for generating and working with log files.
     * [https://github.com/basho/lager]lager - A logging framework for
       Erlang/OTP.
     * [https://github.com/jbrisbin/lager_amqp_backend]lager_amqp_backend
       - AMQP RabbitMQ Lager backend.
     * [https://github.com/synlay/lager_hipchat]lager_hipchat - HipChat
       backend for lager.
     * [https://github.com/kivra/lager_loggly]lager_loggly - Loggly
       backend for lager.
     * [https://github.com/blinkov/lager_smtp]lager_smtp - SMTP backend
       for lager.
     * [https://github.com/heroku/logplex]logplex - Heroku log router.

Monitoring

   Libraries for gathering metrics and monitoring.
     * [https://github.com/mazenharake/entop]entop - A top-like Erlang
       node monitoring tool.
     * [https://github.com/massemanet/eper]eper - A loose collection of
       Erlang Performance related tools.
     * [https://github.com/Feuerlabs/exometer]Exometer - An Erlang
       instrumentation package.
     * [https://github.com/boundary/folsom]folsom - An Erlang based
       metrics system inspired by Coda Hale's
       [https://github.com/codahale/metrics]metrics.
     * [https://github.com/lpgauth/statsderl]statsderl - A statsd Erlang
       client.
     * [https://github.com/ferd/vmstats]vmstats - Tiny Erlang app that
       works in conjunction with statsderl in order to generate
       information on the Erlang VM for graphite logs.

Deployment

   Libraries and tools related to deployment of Erlang/OTP applications.
     * [https://github.com/synlay/docker-erlang]docker-erlang - Basic
       Docker Container Images for Erlang/OTP.

Distributed Systems

   Tools for stress/load testing, latency issues, etc. across
   microservices.
     * [https://github.com/zalando/typhoon]Typhoon - Stress and load
       testing tool for distributed systems that simulates traffic from a
       test cluster toward a system-under-test (SUT) and visualizes
       related latencies.

Code Analysis

   Libraries and tools for analysing, parsing and manipulation codebases.
     * [https://github.com/parapluu/Concuerror]Concuerror - Concuerror is
       a systematic testing tool for concurrent Erlang programs.
     * [https://github.com/proger/eflame]eflame - A Flame Graph profiler
       for Erlang.

Build Tools

   Project build and automation tools.
     * [https://github.com/rebar/rebar]rebar - Erlang build tool that
       makes it easy to compile and test Erlang applications, port drivers
       and releases.
     * [https://github.com/rebar/rebar3]rebar3 - A build tool for Erlang
       which can manage Erlang packages from [https://hex.pm/]Hex.pm. See
       more at [https://www.rebar3.org/]rebar3.org
     * [https://github.com/rustyio/sync]sync - On-the-fly recompiling for
       Erlang.

Geolocation

   Libraries for geocoding addresses and working with latitudes and
   longitudes.
     * [https://github.com/armon/erl-rstar]erl-rstar - An Erlang
       implementation of the R*-tree spacial data structure.
     * [https://github.com/couchbase/geocouch]GeoCouch - A spatial
       extension for Couchbase and Apache CouchDB.
     * [https://github.com/armon/teles]Teles - An Erlang network service
       for manipulating geographic data.

Debugging

   Libraries and tools for debugging code and applications.
     * [https://github.com/kvakvs/tx]tx - An HTML Erlang term viewer,
       starts own webserver and displays any term you give it from your
       Erlang node.

Actors

   Libraries and tools for working with actors and such.
     * [https://github.com/devinus/poolboy]poolboy - A hunky Erlang worker
       pool factory.

Date and Time

   Libraries for working with dates and times.
     * [https://github.com/dmitryme/erlang_localtime]erlang_localtime -
       Erlang library for conversion from one local time to another.
     * [https://github.com/choptastic/qdate]qdate - Erlang date, time, and
       timezone management: formatting, conversion, and date arithmetic.

ORM and Datamapping

   Libraries that implement object-relational mapping or datamapping
   techniques.
     * [https://github.com/ErlyORM/boss_db]boss_db - A sharded, caching,
       pooling, evented ORM for Erlang.
     * [https://github.com/epgsql/epgsql]epgsql - PostgreSQL Driver for
       Erlang.
     * [https://github.com/mysql-otp/mysql-otp]mysql-otp - MySQL/OTP -
       MySQL driver for Erlang/OTP.
     * [https://github.com/artemeff/pgsql_migration]pgsql_migration -
       PostgreSQL migrations for Erlang.

Queue

   Libraries for working with event and task queues.
     * [https://github.com/darach/dq]dq - Distributed Fault Tolerant Queue
       library.
     * [https://github.com/rgrinberg/ebqueue]ebqueue - Tiny simple
       blocking queue in erlang.
     * [https://github.com/okeuday/pqueue]pqueue - Erlang Priority Queues.
     * [https://github.com/ChicagoBoss/tinymq]tinymq - A diminutive,
       in-memory message queue for Erlang.

Authentication

   Libraries for implementing authentications schemes.
     * [https://github.com/kivra/oauth2]oauth2 - Erlang Oauth2
       implementation.

Text and Numbers

   Libraries for parsing and manipulating text and numbers.
     * [https://github.com/artemeff/eql]eql - Erlang with SQL or not.
     * [https://github.com/davisp/jiffy]jiffy - JSON NIFs for Erlang.
     * [https://github.com/talentdeficit/jsx]jsx - An erlang application
       for consuming, producing and manipulating json.
     * [https://github.com/expelledboy/miffy]miffy - Jiffy wrapper which
       returns pretty maps.
     * [https://github.com/artemeff/qsp]qsp - Enhanced query string parser
       for Erlang.
     * [https://github.com/lordnull/rec2json]rec2json - Generate JSON
       encoder/decoder from record specs.

REST and API

   Libraries and web tools for developing REST-ful APIs.
     * [https://github.com/s1n4/leptus]leptus - Leptus is an Erlang REST
       framework that runs on top of cowboy.

Caching

   Libraries for caching data.
     * [https://github.com/fogfish/cache]cache - In-memory Segmented Cache

Third Party APIs

   Libraries for accessing third party APIs.
     * [https://github.com/kivra/restclient]restc - An Erlang REST client
     * [https://github.com/kivra/oauth2_client]oauth2c - An Erlang oAuth 2
       client (uses restc)

Networking

   Libraries and tools for using network related stuff.
     * [https://github.com/benoitc-attic/barrel_tcp]barrel_tcp -
       barrel_tcp is a generic TCP acceptor pool with low latency in
       Erlang.
     * [https://github.com/priestjim/gen_rpc]gen_rpc - A scalable RPC
       library for Erlang-VM based languages.
     * [https://github.com/rpt/gen_tcp_server]gen_tcp_server - A library
       that takes the concept of gen_server and introduces the same
       mechanics for operating a TCP server.
     * [https://github.com/gossiperl/gossiperl]gossiperl - Language
       agnostic gossip middleware and message bus written in Erlang.
     * [https://github.com/benoitc/nat_upnp]nat_upnp - Erlang library to
       map your internal port to an external using UNP IGD.
     * [https://github.com/ninenines/ranch]ranch - Socket acceptor pool
       for TCP protocols.

Internet of Things

   Libraries and tools for interacting with the physical world.
     * [https://github.com/noam-io/lemma_erlang]lemma_erlang - A lemma for
       IDEO's Noam internet-of-things prototyping platform.

Algorithms and Datastructures

   Libraries and implementations of algorithms and datastructures.
     * [https://github.com/fogfish/datum]datum - A pure functional and
       generic programming for Erlang
     * [https://github.com/travelping/erlando]erlando - A set of syntax
       extensions like currying and monads for Erlang.
     * [https://github.com/mochi/statebox]statebox - Erlang state "monad"
       with merge/conflict-resolution capabilities.
     * [https://github.com/basho/riak_dt]riak_dt - Erlang library of state
       based CRDTs.

Translations and Internationalizations

   Libraries providing translations or internationalizations.

Miscellaneous

   Useful libraries or tools that don't fit in the categories above.
     * [https://github.com/ferd/erlang-history]erlang-history - Hacks to
       add shell history to Erlang's shell.
     * [https://github.com/ShoreTel-Inc/erld]erld - erld is a small
       program designed to solve the problem of running Erlang programs as
       a UNIX daemon.

Resources

   Various resources, such as books, websites and articles, for improving
   your Erlang development skills and knowledge.

Websites

   Useful web and Erlang-related websites and newsletters.
     * [https://github.com/0xAX/erlang-bookmarks/wiki/Erlang-bookmarks]Erl
       ang Bookmarks - All about erlang programming language [powerd by
       community].
     * [https://erlangcentral.org/]Erlang Central - An awesome collections
       of erlang resource along with live community chat for discussing
       and seeking help.
     * [http://www.planeterlang.com/]Planet Erlang - Planet site/RSS feed
       of blog posts covering topics across the Erlang ecosystem.
     * [http://spawnedshelter.com/]Spawned Shelter - Erlang Spawned
       Shelter. A collection of the best articles, videos and
       presentations related to Erlang.

Books

   Fantastic books and e-books.
     * [https://leanpub.com/erlangandelixirforimperativeprogrammers]Erlang
       and Elixir for Imperative Programmers - Introduction to Erlang and
       Elixir in the context of functional concepts by Wolfgang Loder
       (2016)
     * [http://learnyousomeerlang.com/]Learn You Some Erlang - Learn you
       some Erlang - for great good! A very thorough resource covering
       everything from beginning Erlang programming to large-scale
       development and deployment.
     * [http://www.erlang-in-anger.com/]Stuff Goes Bad - ERLANG IN ANGER -
       This book intends to be a little guide about how to be the Erlang
       medic in a time of war.

Web Reading

   General web-development-related reading materials.

Erlang Reading

   Erlang-releated reading materials.
     * [http://www.evanmiller.org/joy-of-erlang.html]The Joy of Erlang;
       Or, How To Ride A Toruk - The Joy of Erlang; Or, How To Ride A
       Toruk A fast track introduction to Erlang that teaches the language
       by walking through a few example projects.

Screencasts

   Cool video tutorials.

